<p>——- ——- ———— ——— —– Win Draw Draw Loss Male 40 30 50 120 Woman 40 10 30 80 80 40 80 200 ——- ——- ———— ——— —–</p>
<p>In this sample were 120 men and 80 women; 80 of them predicted a win for the Dutch national team, 40 a draw and 80 loss. If gender and prediction were independent, how many men predicting a win would you expect based on these numbers?</p>
